description: These egg and chilli wraps are a satisfying and tasty replacement for tortilla wraps with a zingy and fresh prawn filling.
keywords: Egg dishes,Pescatarian,Prawn,Gluten free,Tree nut free,Egg,Sesame free,Soy free,Wheat free,Spinach,Dairy free,Peanut free
name: Coriander & Chilli Prawn Egg Wraps Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Whisk the eggs with the diced chilli and half of the coriander. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, non-stick pan on medium heat. Pour in 1/8th of the egg mix and swirl to coat the pan in a thin layer. Cook for 2 minutes on each side and repeat with the rest of the egg mix to make 8 wraps. Set aside to cool.
Fill each wrap with prawns, spinach, spring onions, coriander and bean sprouts. Serve open or folded up with sweet chilli sauce for dipping.
